servings: 2
---

1 olive oil
2 potato
1 carrot
½ sachet dried oregano
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 egg
½ packet fine breadcrumbs
1 cucumber
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks. Slice carrot
into thick rounds.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle
with olive oil, then add dried oregano (see
ingredients) and season with salt and pepper.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until
tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Help toss the veggies.

• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if
you're sensitive to heat!
• In a large bowl, add beef & pork mince, garlic
paste, Louisiana spice blend, the egg, grated
Parmesan cheese and fine breadcrumbs (see
ingredients). Season with pepper and combine.

• Using damp hands, form heaped spoonfuls of
mince mixture into meatballs (3-4 per person),
then flatten to make 1cm-thick rissoles. Transfer
to a plate.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook rissoles in batches, until browned all over
and cooked through, 4-5 minutes each side.

• While the rissoles are cooking, roughly chop
cucumber.
• In a second large bowl, combine cucumber and
mixed salad leaves. Add a drizzle of white wine
vinegar and olive oil and toss to coat. Season
to taste.

Little cooks: Kids can help combine the ingredients
for the salad!

• Divide beef and pork rissoles and roast veggie
chunks between plates.
• Serve with cucumber salad and smokey aioli.
Enjoy!